<stack-static>
    <statement><p><p>
The acidity of a solution is measured using pH, defined as:
<me>
\text{pH} = -\text{log} [H^+]
</me>
</p>

<p>
A solution has hydrogen ion concentration:
</p>

<p>
<me>
[H^+] = 10^{-{5}}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Find the pH of the solution.
</p>

<p>
<fillin characters="8" name="ans1"/>  
</p></p></statement>
    <solution><p><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We are given:
</p>

<p>
<me>
[H^+] = 10^{-{5}}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 1: Apply the pH formula:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\text{pH} = -\text{log}(10^{-{5}})
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 2: Use logarithm rule:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\text{log}(10^x) = x
</me>
</p>

<p>
<me>
\text{log}(10^{-{5}}) = -{5}
</me>
</p>

<p>
Step 3: Apply the negative sign:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\text{pH} = -(-{5}) = {5}
</me>
</p></p></solution>
    <answer><p><m>5</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>